02:14.612 --> 02:17.528
-DISPATCH: 295, POSSIBLE
SUBMERSION AT SUNSET BEACH.

02:17.659 --> 02:19.574
CAROLINE REQUEST ALL
AVAILABLE ASSISTANCE.

02:26.972 --> 02:28.017
-SHERYL: THIS
WATER'S SO MURKY,

02:28.148 --> 02:29.540
IT'S HARD TO
SEE ANYTHING.

02:31.673 --> 02:33.196
-J.D.: JUST KEEP LOOKING.

02:36.025 --> 02:39.028
-[SIRENS]

02:51.649 --> 02:54.913
-I'M SORRY, I COULDN'T FIND
THEM, I COULDN'T FIND THEM.

02:55.044 --> 02:56.698
-DISPATCH SAYS YOU GOT
A POSSIBLE SUBMERSION.

02:56.828 --> 02:58.395
-J.D. AND CHERYL, THEY'RE
STILL OUT THERE LOOKING.

02:58.526 --> 03:00.484
[WOMAN SPEAKING IN SPANISH]

03:00.615 --> 03:02.878
-ONE MOMENT,
NO HABLA ESPAÑOL.
HABLE INGLES?

03:03.008 --> 03:04.358
-NO, THEY DON'T
SPEAK ENGLISH, MITCH.

03:04.488 --> 03:06.142
-WHAT HAPPENED?
-[SIRENS]

03:06.273 --> 03:07.099
-OH LOOK, THERE'S MANNY,
HE'LL BE ABLE TO TRANSLATE.

03:07.230 --> 03:08.884
-MITCH: WHAT HAPPENED?

03:09.014 --> 03:10.277
-ALL I KNOW IS I'M HEADING
BACK TOWARDS HEADQUARTERS

03:10.407 --> 03:11.539
AND I SEE THEM
RUNNING UP TOWARDS ME.

03:11.669 --> 03:13.454
THEY'RE WAVING
ME TO STOP.

03:13.584 --> 03:15.456
THEY BEGGED ME TO GO IN THE
WATER, SO I CALL IN A CODE R,

03:15.586 --> 03:17.458
I GO IN THE WATER, BUT
MITCH, I CAN'T FIND ANYTHING.

03:17.588 --> 03:18.981
I DON'T EVEN KNOW
WHAT I'M LOOKING FOR.

03:19.111 --> 03:20.417
-MANNY, LOOK, THESE GUYS
DON'T SPEAK ENGLISH.

03:20.548 --> 03:21.462
TALK TO THEM, ASK
THEM WHAT HAPPENED?

03:21.592 --> 03:25.335
-[MANNY SPEAKING SPANISH]

03:25.466 --> 03:30.993
-[WOMAN SPEAKING SPANISH]

03:31.733 --> 03:32.516
-HER DAUGHTER, ROSANNA,
WENT IN THE WATER

03:32.647 --> 03:33.952
AND SHE NEVER CAME OUT.

03:34.083 --> 03:35.737
-WHEN WAS THE LAST
TIME THEY SAW HER?

03:35.867 --> 03:38.000
-[MANNY SPEAKING IN SPANISH]

03:38.130 --> 03:41.656
-[WOMAN SPEAKING IN SPANISH]

03:41.786 --> 03:44.049
-SHE DIDN'T SEE HER GO
IN, THE LITTLE GIRL DID.

03:46.487 --> 03:50.926
[MANNY SPEAKING IN SPANISH]

03:59.151 --> 04:01.328
-[LITTLE GIRL
SPEAKING IN SPANISH]

04:03.025 --> 04:05.680
-MANNY: HER SISTER WAS VERY
SAD, BUT SHE WOULDN'T SAY WHY.

04:06.246 --> 04:07.986
SHE SAID THAT SHE
WOULDN'T UNDERSTAND.

04:28.572 --> 04:32.707
-[LITTLE GIRL
SPEAKING IN SPANISH]

04:33.403 --> 04:34.926
-MANNY: WHEN THE LIFEGUARD
LEFT, ROSANNA GOT UP

04:35.057 --> 04:36.319
AND WENT INTO THE WATER.

04:36.450 --> 04:37.625
-ROSANNA!

04:37.755 --> 04:40.323
[SPEAKING IN
SPANISH] ROSANNA.

04:42.760 --> 04:47.199
ROSANNA, ROSANNA
[SPEAKING IN SPANISH]!

04:50.202 --> 04:51.508
ROSANNA!

04:54.859 --> 04:56.034
ROSANNA!

05:01.692 --> 05:02.867
ROSANNA!

05:09.004 --> 05:11.049
ROSANNA!

05:11.180 --> 05:14.314
[LITTLE GIRL
SPEAKING IN SPANISH]

05:14.444 --> 05:16.098
-MANNY: SHE NEVER
SAW HER COME OUT.

05:17.012 --> 05:18.318
-MITCH: THAT WAS
CODY'S TOWER, WASN'T IT?

05:18.448 --> 05:19.710
-YEAH, HIS SHIFT
ENDED AT FIVE.

05:19.841 --> 05:22.713
-[SIRENS]

05:22.844 --> 05:24.367
-ALL RIGHT, BRIEF THEM
ON THE WATER CONDITIONS.

05:24.498 --> 05:27.196
OKAY, ASK THEM WHAT THE
MISSING GIRL WAS WEARING,

05:27.327 --> 05:29.198
AND THE EXACT TIME SHE
WENT INTO THE WATER.

05:31.200 --> 05:32.375
-FEMALE 2: ALL
RIGHT, I'M ON MY WAY.

05:32.506 --> 05:33.550
-APRIL: LET'S
GO GUYS, SUIT UP.

05:37.249 --> 05:38.686
-WHAT'S GOIN' ON?

05:38.816 --> 05:40.949
-[SIRENS]

05:46.476 --> 05:47.303
-OKAY STOP!

05:47.434 --> 05:48.260
GOOD.

05:48.391 --> 05:50.001
-YEAH IT'S BUCHANNON.

05:50.132 --> 05:52.526
I WANT ALL AVAILABLE
PERSONNEL TO THE BEACH ASAP.

05:53.788 --> 05:55.442
-YOU GOT A ROCKY BOTTOM,
LOTS OF HOLES GUYS.

05:55.572 --> 05:57.269
WATCH YOUR FOOTING.

05:57.400 --> 05:58.749
VISIBILITY'S NEXT TO NOTHING
UNTIL YOU GET OUT 30 FEET.

05:59.750 --> 06:01.143
-AND GET AHOLD OF TANNER.

06:01.273 --> 06:02.710
NOTIFY THE CHIEF OF
WHAT'S COMING DOWN HERE.

06:02.840 --> 06:04.233
I'LL KEEP YOU POSTED.

06:04.364 --> 06:08.280
-[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]

06:17.028 --> 06:18.334
-J.D.: ALL
RIGHT, NEWMIE.

06:19.074 --> 06:20.031
GO GET HIM MAN.

06:23.252 --> 06:25.167
-I HOPE THEY HAVE
BETTER LUCK THAN WE DID.

06:30.390 --> 06:31.739
-GET IN THE WATER!

06:34.002 --> 06:35.090
[INAUDIBLE YELLING]

06:35.220 --> 06:36.657
8-J.D.: THIS IS GREAT.

06:36.787 --> 06:38.354
WITH MORE DIVERS, WE CAN
EXPAND THE PERIMETER.

06:38.485 --> 06:39.486
-MANNY: MITCH.

06:40.051 --> 06:41.139
SHE SAYS ROSANNA
WENT IN THE WATER

06:41.270 --> 06:42.271
A FEW MINUTES BEFORE FIVE.

06:42.402 --> 06:43.751
-IS SHE SURE ABOUT THAT?

06:43.881 --> 06:45.883
-[MANNY SPEAKING IN SPANISH]

06:46.014 --> 06:51.193
-[WOMAN SPEAKING IN SPANISH]

07:03.727 --> 07:05.337
-MANNY: I NOTICED THE
WINDOW WAS DOWN SO WHEN

07:05.468 --> 07:07.905
I STARTED THE
CAR, IT WAS 4:57.

07:15.217 --> 07:17.045
-IF IT WAS BEFORE FIVE,
THERE SHOULD'VE BEEN

07:17.175 --> 07:18.438
A LIFEGUARD IN THAT TOWER.

07:19.351 --> 07:21.179
-[MANNY SPEAKING SPANISH]

07:21.310 --> 07:24.008
[WOMAN SPEAKING SPANISH]

07:25.183 --> 07:26.054
-THERE WAS NO LIFEGUARD.

07:26.184 --> 07:27.490
THE TOWER WAS CLOSED.

07:32.060 --> 07:32.974
-ROSANNA!

07:34.279 --> 07:37.457
[WOMAN SPEAKING IN SPANISH]

07:37.587 --> 07:38.719
-MANNY: I LOOKED ALL
AROUND FOR ROSANNA.

07:38.849 --> 07:40.372
SHE WAS NOWHERE
TO BE FOUND.

07:41.548 --> 07:46.422
-[WOMAN SPEAKING SPANISH]

07:50.992 --> 07:52.689
-MANNY: I GOT SCARED,
I STARTED TO PANIC

07:52.820 --> 07:54.386
AND RAN FOR HELP.

07:54.517 --> 07:56.258
THAT'S WHEN WE NOTICED
THAT THE TOWER WAS CLOSED.

07:59.130 --> 08:02.612
-[WOMAN SPEAKING SPANISH]

08:04.962 --> 08:06.747
-ALL RIGHT, GO SEE
WHERE SHE PARKED.

08:06.877 --> 08:08.270
MAYBE WE'LL CATCH A BREAK AND
THE LITTLE GIRL WILL BE BACK

08:08.400 --> 08:09.793
WAITING AT THE CAR, HUH?

08:09.924 --> 08:11.099
-OKAY.

08:12.492 --> 08:13.449
-UNO MOMENTO POR FAVOR.

08:13.580 --> 08:14.406
OKAY?

08:14.537 --> 08:15.582
IT'S OKAY, IT'S OKAY.

08:21.631 --> 08:22.458
-BOO!

08:22.589 --> 08:23.590
HEY.

08:24.460 --> 08:25.809
WHAT, WHAT'S WRONG?

08:25.940 --> 08:26.984
-WE JUST GOT CALLED
INTO HEADQUARTERS.

08:27.115 --> 08:28.159
-YOU'RE KIDDING ME.

08:28.290 --> 08:29.378
WHAT'S THE PROBLEM?

08:29.509 --> 08:30.771
-I DON'T KNOW.

08:33.121 --> 08:34.208
-LET'S GO.

08:34.775 --> 08:39.996
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

09:02.063 --> 09:05.457
-[SIRENS]

09:05.588 --> 09:07.503
-ACCORDING TO WITNESSES
SHE WAS WEARING A BLACK

09:07.634 --> 09:10.027
T-SHIRT AND
BLUE JEAN SHORTS.

09:12.943 --> 09:14.466
[SIGHS]

09:16.120 --> 09:16.991
APRIL!

09:18.122 --> 09:19.863
SET UP THE PERIMETER.

09:19.994 --> 09:21.256
-HOW DID THEY
GET HERE SO FAST?

09:21.386 --> 09:22.257
-MITCH: THEY GOT
SCANNERS, THEY'RE

09:22.387 --> 09:23.475
MONITORING OUR FREQUENCY.

09:23.606 --> 09:24.955
-[HELICOPTER BUZZING]

09:28.959 --> 09:30.221
-GREAT.

09:45.236 --> 09:46.629
-HEY WHAT'S GOING ON?

09:46.760 --> 09:47.587
-LOOKS LIKE WE GOT
A POSSIBLE SUBMERSION

09:47.717 --> 09:48.588
ON SUNSET BEACH.

09:49.153 --> 09:49.937
-SUNSET BEACH?

09:50.067 --> 09:50.851
WHAT TOWER?

09:50.981 --> 09:51.939
-YOURS.

09:52.069 --> 09:56.813
-[OMINOUS MUSIC]

09:59.424 --> 10:01.339
-MAN: PLEASE STAY
BACK BEHIND THE LINE!

10:02.079 --> 10:03.951
-ALRIGHT LET'S FIND OUT
WHO'S IN CHARGE HERE.

10:04.908 --> 10:06.693
-THIS WHOLE THING IS
TURNING INTO A MEDIA CIRCUS.

10:06.823 --> 10:09.173
GET ME SOME MORE
PERSONNEL OUT HERE ASAP.

10:10.914 --> 10:12.133
-MITCH, SHE
WASN'T AT THE CAR.

10:12.263 --> 10:13.700
ALL HER STUFF
WAS STILL INSIDE.

10:13.830 --> 10:15.615
DOESN'T LOOK LIKE
SHE'S GONNA COME BACK.

10:15.745 --> 10:18.879
-[WOMAN SPEAKING IN SPANISH]

10:19.009 --> 10:20.010
-[INAUDIBLE] WHAT'S SHE SAYING?

10:20.141 --> 10:21.490
-SHE'S FREAKING OUT.

10:21.621 --> 10:22.404
-LOOK, JUST TALK,
TRY TO COMFORT HER.

10:22.534 --> 10:23.535
TELL HER TO CALM DOWN.

10:23.666 --> 10:24.754
WE'LL FIND
THE LITTLE GIRL.

10:24.885 --> 10:25.450
KEEP HER AWAY
FROM THE MEDIA.

10:25.581 --> 10:26.713
-SIR, SIR.

10:26.843 --> 10:28.540
EXCUSE ME, ARE
YOU THE MAN HERE?

10:28.671 --> 10:29.237
-I'M THE INCIDENT COMMANDER.
-WHAT'S YOUR NAME PLEASE?

10:29.367 --> 10:30.934
-UH, BUCHANNON--

10:31.065 --> 10:31.892
-I'M SORRY, ONE SECOND.
CAN YOU GET THE SHOT PLEASE?

10:32.022 --> 10:33.633
THANK YOU.

10:33.763 --> 10:35.069
OKAY LET'S TRY IT AGAIN.
YOUR NAME, SIR, AGAIN, PLEASE?

10:35.199 --> 10:36.461
-LOOK I DON'T HAVE
TIME FOR THIS RIGHT NOW.

10:36.592 --> 10:37.985
-JUST A COUPLE OF
QUICK QUESTIONS.

10:38.115 --> 10:38.550
FIRST OF ALL, HAVE YOU
FOUND THE BODY YET?

10:39.900 --> 10:41.336
WHAT ARE THE CHANCES THIS
LITTLE GIRL'S STILL ALIVE

10:41.466 --> 10:42.250
OUT HERE, I MEAN HOW LONG
COULD SOMEBODY SURVIVE

10:42.380 --> 10:43.860
IN THESE WATERS?

10:43.991 --> 10:45.688
-WE DON'T EVEN KNOW IF
SHE'S OUT THERE, OKAY?

10:45.819 --> 10:47.124
WILL YOU EXCUSE ME, I'VE GOT A
RESCUE OPERATION TO COORDINATE.

10:47.255 --> 10:48.343
-BUT SIR, ONE MORE QUESTION!

10:48.473 --> 10:49.474
PLEASE, SIR JUST ONE MORE!

10:49.605 --> 10:50.432
-[SIRENS]

10:50.562 --> 10:51.607
-EXCUSE ME!

10:51.738 --> 10:53.130
EXCUSE ME PLEASE!

10:54.088 --> 10:55.263
I NEED TO TALK
TO YOU, COME HERE.

10:56.525 --> 10:57.831
-IT'S GONNA BE
OKAY, ALL RIGHT?

10:58.353 --> 10:59.920
WE'RE DOING THE
BEST WE CAN.

11:00.050 --> 11:01.051
-DO YOU HAVE ANY
HOPE OF FINDING--

11:01.182 --> 11:02.357
-EXCUSE ME, PLEASE!

11:06.143 --> 11:07.449
WERE THEY ON
YOUR BEACH TODAY?

11:07.579 --> 11:09.059
-YUP.

11:09.190 --> 11:10.582
THERE WAS ANOTHER GIRL
WITH THEM, A TEENAGER.

11:10.713 --> 11:12.106
SHE THE ONE
WHO'S MISSING?

11:12.236 --> 11:13.194
-YEAH.

11:13.760 --> 11:14.586
YOU SEE HER GO
IN THE WATER?

11:14.717 --> 11:15.892
-NO.

11:16.023 --> 11:16.980
I REMEMBER BECAUSE
THEY WERE HAVING

11:17.111 --> 11:18.199
A PRETTY NASTY ARGUMENT.

11:18.329 --> 11:20.244
I WAS GONNA SAY
SOMETHING BUT

11:20.375 --> 11:22.072
I FIGURED IT WAS BEST
TO MIND MY OWN BUSINESS.

11:22.203 --> 11:23.770
ESPECIALLY SINCE THEY
WEREN'T PAYIN' MUCH ATTENTION

11:23.900 --> 11:25.119
TO THAT LITTLE GIRL.

11:25.249 --> 11:29.776
-[BOTH WOMEN
ARGUING IN SPANISH]

11:54.931 --> 11:57.717
-[PHONE RINGING]

12:02.765 --> 12:03.940
YEAH, THIS IS MADISON.

12:04.071 --> 12:04.941
-LANI:
HEY IT'S LANI.

12:05.072 --> 12:06.116
-HEY BABY.

12:06.247 --> 12:07.901
-UM, I JUST GOT
THE TICKETS BUT

12:08.031 --> 12:09.946
THE MOVIE STARTS AT 5:15,
CAN YOU GET HERE BY THEN?

12:10.077 --> 12:11.426
-YEAH NO PROBLEM
I GOT MY BIKE.

12:11.556 --> 12:13.210
-ALL RIGHT WELL JUST
TRY TO HURRY OKAY

12:13.341 --> 12:14.646
BECAUSE I DON'T WANNA
GET STUCK IN FRONT ROW.

12:14.777 --> 12:15.952
-OKAY.
I'LL SEE YA THERE.

12:16.083 --> 12:17.519
-ALL RIGHT, BYE.

12:23.612 --> 12:28.573
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

12:43.893 --> 12:45.852
-[CODY GRUNTS]

13:01.389 --> 13:02.433
-MITCH: WHAT TIME'D
YOUR SHIFT END?

13:02.564 --> 13:03.783
-FIVE.

13:04.435 --> 13:05.785
-WHAT TIME'D YOU
LEAVE THE TOWER?

13:12.487 --> 13:13.705
THE REASON I'M ASKING IS

13:13.836 --> 13:15.142
BECAUSE THE
LITTLE GIRL'S MOTHER

13:15.272 --> 13:17.405
SAID SHE LOOKED AT
THE CLOCK AT 4:57

13:17.535 --> 13:19.624
AND THERE WAS NOBODY IN
THE TOWER AND I'M WONDERING

13:19.755 --> 13:21.365
HOW COULD
THAT POSSIBLY BE?

13:23.150 --> 13:25.195
-I SET MY WATCH
FIVE MINUTES FAST

13:25.326 --> 13:26.370
SO I DON'T RUN LATE.

13:27.763 --> 13:29.417
LOOK, MITCH, I'M SORRY.

13:29.547 --> 13:31.419
WHEN I LEFT THE BEACH, SHE
WAS SITTING ON A BLANKET!

13:32.028 --> 13:33.334
THE WIND WAS BLOWING,
IT WAS GETTING COLD.

13:33.464 --> 13:34.639
NOBODY WAS
GOING IN THE WATER.

13:35.553 --> 13:36.728
HELL SHE WASN'T EVEN
WEARING A BATHING SUIT!

13:36.859 --> 13:37.904
-DOESN'T MATTER!

13:38.034 --> 13:39.862
YOU NEVER, EVER
LEAVE YOUR TOWER

13:39.993 --> 13:40.820
BEFORE YOUR SHIFT
IS OVER, PERIOD!

13:40.950 --> 13:42.082
YOU KNOW THE RULES!

13:42.212 --> 13:43.561
-MITCH!

13:43.692 --> 13:44.824
MITCH, IT WAS JUST
AS MUCH MY FAULT.

13:44.954 --> 13:46.390
I'M THE ONE
THAT CALLED CODY.

13:46.521 --> 13:47.957
I TOLD HIM TO HURRY.

13:48.088 --> 13:50.090
I JUST BOUGHT THESE
TICKETS FOR A 5:15 MOVIE

13:50.220 --> 13:51.482
AND I DIDN'T WANT
HIM TO BE LATE.

13:51.613 --> 13:52.875
-I DON'T BELIEVE
I'M HEARING THIS.

13:53.006 --> 13:54.224
YOU'RE TELLING ME
BECAUSE OF A MOVIE

13:54.355 --> 13:55.399
A LITTLE GIRL'S LIFE
IS AT RISK HERE?

13:55.530 --> 13:56.748
GO ON, GET OUT OF HERE!

13:56.879 --> 13:57.662
GET OUT OF HERE!
TURN THAT THING OFF!

13:57.793 --> 13:59.099
GET OUT OF HERE!

13:59.795 --> 14:00.970
JUST TRYIN' TO
DO OUR JOB HERE.

14:01.101 --> 14:04.191
-[WOMAN SCREAMS IN SPANISH]

14:23.863 --> 14:28.345
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

14:40.009 --> 14:42.664
-IF YOU NEED NEW FINS,
GET BACK UP ON THE SHORE!

14:42.794 --> 14:44.361
THEY GOT SOME
EXTRA PAIRS!

15:06.557 --> 15:07.645
-MAN: NEWMAN!

15:07.776 --> 15:08.516
WE NEED TO HOOK
UP THE TOW BAR.

15:08.646 --> 15:09.386
CAN YOU GIVE ME A HAND?

15:09.517 --> 15:10.605
-GOTCHA.

15:17.046 --> 15:18.178
-HERE YOU GO
GUYS, I THOUGHT

15:18.308 --> 15:18.874
YOU MIGHT LIKE
SOMETHING TO EAT.

15:19.483 --> 15:24.271
-[MANNY SPEAKING IN SPANISH]

15:35.978 --> 15:36.848
-APRIL: HOLD ON
I'LL GET HIM.

15:36.979 --> 15:37.893
MITCH!

15:38.024 --> 15:38.938
I HAVE THE CHIEF FOR YOU.

15:40.026 --> 15:41.505
-YEAH, THIS IS BUCHANNON.

15:41.636 --> 15:43.333
DON'T GO ANYWHERE, I'M
NOT DONE WITH YOU YET.

15:44.030 --> 15:45.074
-CHIEF: WHAT'S THE
STORY MITCH, DO YOU

15:45.205 --> 15:46.554
HAVE A SUBMERSION OR NOT?

15:46.684 --> 15:48.208
-NOTHING CONFIRMED
BUT WE'RE OPERATING

15:48.338 --> 15:49.731
ON THE ASSUMPTION THAT
SOMEONE'S STILL OUT THERE.

15:49.861 --> 15:51.689
-CHIEF: I'M SITTING IN
MY OFFICE WATCHING THIS

15:51.820 --> 15:53.474
WHOLE THING ON TV.

15:53.604 --> 15:54.866
THEY'RE CARRYING YOU LIVE
ON ALL THE LOCAL CHANNELS.

15:55.476 --> 15:57.521
-TALK ABOUT OPERATING
IN A FISHBOWL, HUH?

15:57.652 --> 15:58.958
-CHIEF: I JUST SAW
YOU ALMOST BITE SOME

15:59.088 --> 16:00.089
REPORTER'S HEAD OFF!

16:01.177 --> 16:02.048
-CAROLINE!

16:02.744 --> 16:04.920
YOU NEVER, EVER
LEAVE YOUR TOWER

16:05.051 --> 16:06.052
BEFORE YOUR SHIFT
IS OVER, PERIOD!

16:06.182 --> 16:07.488
YOU KNOW THE RULES!

16:07.618 --> 16:08.793
-LANI: IT WAS JUST
AS MUCH MY FAULT.

16:08.924 --> 16:09.664
I'M THE ONE
THAT CALLED CODY.

16:09.794 --> 16:11.187
I TOLD HIM TO HURRY.

16:11.318 --> 16:12.797
I JUST BOUGHT THESE
TICKETS FOR A 5:15 MOVIE

16:12.928 --> 16:14.234
AND I DIDN'T WANT
HIM TO BE LATE.

16:14.364 --> 16:15.148
-MITCH: I DON'T
BELIEVE I'M HEARING THIS.

16:15.278 --> 16:16.671
-OH MAN!

16:16.801 --> 16:18.107
-MITCH: A LITTLE GIRL'S LIFE
IS AT RISK HERE?

16:18.238 --> 16:19.195
-[SIGHS]
-MITCH: TURN THAT

16:19.326 --> 16:20.718
DAMN THING OFF!
-OH MAN!

16:20.849 --> 16:23.460
HEY, KID, YOU GOT A BIG
FUTURE IN THIS BUSINESS,

16:23.591 --> 16:24.548
LEMME TELL YA.

16:25.506 --> 16:27.029
AND SO DO I.

16:27.160 --> 16:28.900
[LAUGHS]

16:29.640 --> 16:31.251
-MITCH, WHY ARE YOU
DOING THIS--

16:31.381 --> 16:32.774
-BECAUSE YOU'RE USED TO
BEING IN FRONT OF THE CAMERAS.

16:32.904 --> 16:33.644
-I'M GOOD WITH A
SCRIPT, ALL RIGHT?

16:33.775 --> 16:35.342
I NEED LINES.

16:35.472 --> 16:36.386
I DON'T HAVE ANY LINES,
I'M NOT GOOD AT WINGING IT!

16:36.517 --> 16:37.474
WHAT AM I SUPPOSED TO SAY?

16:37.605 --> 16:38.519
-JUST ANSWER THE QUESTIONS!

16:38.649 --> 16:39.868
-GOD, I'M GONNA BE ON TV.

16:39.999 --> 16:41.043
HOW'S MY HAIR?

16:41.174 --> 16:42.740
-"HOW'S MY?" [SIGHS]

16:42.871 --> 16:44.220
-OKAY, HERE SHE COMES.

16:44.351 --> 16:45.526
WHAT'S THE LATEST
ON THE LITTLE GIRL?

16:45.656 --> 16:46.527
-YEAH, EXCUSE ME.

16:46.657 --> 16:47.528
WAIT A MINUTE.

16:48.311 --> 16:49.878
ALL RIGHT, MY NAME IS
CAROLINE HOLDEN AND

16:50.009 --> 16:52.489
I'M A SENIOR OCEAN
LIFEGUARD HERE AT BAYWATCH

16:52.620 --> 16:55.144
AND I'LL TRY AND ANSWER
ANY QUESTIONS YOU MIGHT

16:55.275 --> 16:56.189
HAVE AT THIS TIME.

16:56.319 --> 16:57.451
-[BOTH REPORTERS TALKING]

16:57.581 --> 16:58.495
-BOTH REPORTERS:
EXCUSE ME!

16:58.626 --> 17:03.283
-[BOTH REPORTERS TALKING]

17:06.329 --> 17:10.594
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

17:18.733 --> 17:19.994
-SCARAB ONE, STAY NORTH.

17:20.126 --> 17:21.257
STAY NORTH!

17:21.387 --> 17:22.345
--MITCH.

17:23.303 --> 17:24.955
I JUST FOUND OUT THAT THE
MISSING GIRL WAS HAVING PROBLEMS

17:25.087 --> 17:26.480
WITH HER BOYFRIEND.

17:26.609 --> 17:27.655
HER MOTHER BROUGHT
HER HERE TO MEET HIM,

17:27.785 --> 17:29.483
ONLY HE NEVER SHOWS UP.

17:29.613 --> 17:30.919
SO SHE WASN'T IN THE
BEST FRAME OF MIND.

17:31.050 --> 17:32.747
-ALL RIGHT
THANKS, THANKS.

17:35.793 --> 17:39.536
-[MAN YELLING
ON MEGAPHONE]

17:40.711 --> 17:42.713
-WELL YES, PERSONALLY
I HAVE BEEN INVOLVED

17:42.844 --> 17:45.107
IN CASES WHERE THE VICTIM
HAS BEEN REVIVED AFTER

17:45.238 --> 17:46.891
45 MINUTES OF
BEING IN THE WATER.

17:47.414 --> 17:49.198
SO TO ANSWER YOUR
QUESTION, THIS IS VERY MUCH

17:49.329 --> 17:50.765
A RESCUE OPERATION.

17:50.895 --> 17:53.072
WE HAVE EVERY HOPE OF
FINDING THIS GIRL ALIVE.

17:53.202 --> 17:54.073
-[BOTH REPORTERS TALKING]

17:54.203 --> 17:54.986
-THANK YOU, THAT'S IT.

17:55.117 --> 17:57.598
-[REPORTERS CHATTER]

18:16.007 --> 18:17.226
-THIS IS ALL
THAT'S LEFT.

18:17.357 --> 18:18.271
I'M NOT SURE THESE
FINS WILL FIT.

18:23.102 --> 18:23.928
CODY?

18:25.016 --> 18:26.105
DID YOU HEAR
WHAT I SAID?

18:27.410 --> 18:28.759
-[GIRL CRYING
OUT IN SPANISH]

18:28.890 --> 18:29.847
-THAT'S HER.

18:32.415 --> 18:33.460
THERE SHE IS!

18:33.590 --> 18:35.070
SHE'S RIGHT THERE!

18:35.679 --> 18:36.506
J.D.!

18:36.637 --> 18:37.986
-SHE'S RIGHT THERE!

18:42.251 --> 18:43.252
J.D.!

18:46.168 --> 18:47.604
-CODY!

18:47.735 --> 18:49.040
BABY, ARE YOU OKAY?

18:51.478 --> 18:52.827
BABY, WHAT'S WRONG?

18:55.612 --> 18:57.136
-SHE WAS RIGHT THERE.

18:58.572 --> 18:59.442
-WHERE IS SHE?

19:00.704 --> 19:02.010
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

19:02.141 --> 19:03.272
-COME ON, LET'S GO.

19:05.840 --> 19:07.146
-SHE WAS RIGHT THERE.

19:09.017 --> 19:09.887
-COME ON.

19:17.068 --> 19:18.069
COME ON BABE.

19:19.767 --> 19:20.855
-CODY: AM I LOSIN' IT?

19:29.168 --> 19:31.257
-I'M AT SUNSET BEACH
WHERE COUNTY LIFEGUARDS ARE

19:31.387 --> 19:33.084
STILL SEARCHING FOR
A SIXTEEN-YEAR-OLD

19:33.215 --> 19:34.695
GIRL, LAST SEEN BY

19:34.825 --> 19:36.827
HER SISTER BEFORE
SLIPPING BELOW THE SURFACE

19:36.958 --> 19:38.742
OF A VERY TURBULENT SEA.

19:38.873 --> 19:41.963
NOW IRONICALLY, THIS TRAGIC
LOSS OF LIFE MAY BE THE RESULT

19:42.529 --> 19:45.488
OF A LIFEGUARD LEAVING
HIS TOWER EARLY IN ORDER

19:45.619 --> 19:47.795
TO KEEP A DATE WITH
HIS GIRLFRIEND.

19:47.925 --> 19:49.971
WE'RE ABOUT TO SHOW YOU
SOME EXCLUSIVE FOOTAGE

19:50.101 --> 19:52.539
OF BAYWATCH LIFEGUARD
CODY MADISON

19:52.669 --> 19:56.717
ADMITTING TO HIS CAPTAIN THAT
HE DID INDEED DESERT HIS POST.

19:56.847 --> 19:58.806
ARE WE READY TO ROLL
THAT VIDEO TAPE?

19:59.372 --> 20:00.503
OKAY.

20:00.634 --> 20:01.504
HERE IT IS.

20:01.635 --> 20:02.462
HEY!

20:02.592 --> 20:03.550
-CODY NO!

20:03.680 --> 20:05.291
-[PEOPLE SHOUTING]

20:05.421 --> 20:06.205
-GET UP!

20:06.335 --> 20:07.118
COME ON, GET UP!

20:07.249 --> 20:08.032
GET UP!

20:08.163 --> 20:09.425
COME ON, GET UP!

20:11.949 --> 20:13.081
-MITCH: HEY, HEY, HEY,
HEY, KNOCK IT OFF!

20:13.212 --> 20:13.995
KNOCK IT OFF!

20:14.125 --> 20:15.257
-YOU'RE INSANE!

20:15.388 --> 20:15.997
-KNOCK IT OFF,
KNOCK IT OFF!

20:16.127 --> 20:16.911
EASY, EASY!

20:17.041 --> 20:18.391
GET OUTTA HERE!

20:18.521 --> 20:19.392
-KEEP THIS ROLLING,
KEEP THIS ROLLING!

20:19.522 --> 20:20.523
-GET OUTTA HERE!

20:20.654 --> 20:21.916
KNOCK IT OFF!

20:22.046 --> 20:23.396
COOL DOWN!

20:23.526 --> 20:24.310
COOL DOWN!

20:24.440 --> 20:25.398
TAKE HIM HOME.

20:27.138 --> 20:28.052
YOU ALL RIGHT?

20:28.183 --> 20:29.140
-YEAH.

20:29.924 --> 20:31.099
-ALL RIGHT.

20:32.318 --> 20:33.884
KEEP THINGS
CALM AROUND HERE.

20:34.885 --> 20:35.973
I'M GOIN' IN THE WATER.

20:39.760 --> 20:45.592
-[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]

22:57.245 --> 22:58.768
-I CALLED THE HOUSE
AGAIN, STILL NO ANSWER.

22:59.856 --> 23:01.075
-WHO ARE THOSE TWO?

23:01.771 --> 23:04.252
-APRIL: THE ONE IN THE BLUE
SHIRT IS ROSANNA'S BOYFRIEND.

23:08.604 --> 23:09.997
-CAROLINE: THAT'S
ABOUT ALL I KNOW.

23:11.999 --> 23:13.740
-CAROLINE, WOULD IT BE
POSSIBLE TO DO AN INTERVIEW?

23:13.870 --> 23:15.306
-YOU KNOW WHAT, I
ACTUALLY NEED TO GET BACK.

23:15.437 --> 23:16.830
-PLEASE, I'M ALL SET
UP, I'VE GOT THE CREW

23:16.960 --> 23:17.874
READY TO GO.

23:18.005 --> 23:18.788
-YEAH, OKAY.

23:18.919 --> 23:20.486
-THANKS.

23:20.616 --> 23:22.313
YOU KNOW, I KNOW THIS IS
A TENSE SITUATION FOR YOU.

23:23.924 --> 23:26.492
BUT I'M TRYING TO GET THE
LIFEGUARD'S POINT OF VIEW.

23:26.622 --> 23:27.449
OKAY?

23:28.450 --> 23:29.625
WE'RE READY TO GO LIVE.

23:30.234 --> 23:32.498
I'M SPEAKING WITH BAYWATCH
LIFEGUARD CAROLINE HOLDEN

23:32.628 --> 23:34.761
WHO WHEN SHE'S NOT
SAVING LIVES, CAN BE SEEN

23:34.891 --> 23:37.154
ON THE HOT NEW DAYTIME
SOAP SHANNON'S HOPE.

23:37.285 --> 23:39.548
OF COURSE TODAY WE'RE DEALING
WITH A REAL LIFE DRAMA,

23:39.679 --> 23:41.158
-CAN YOU TELL ME ABOUT...

23:41.289 --> 23:42.812
CAROLINE?

23:42.943 --> 23:44.510
WELL APPEARS WE HAVE LOST
OUR INTERVIEW SUBJECT..

23:44.640 --> 23:45.467
-CHECK WITH ZUMA.

23:45.598 --> 23:46.729
-FEMALE 2: RIGHT AWAY.

23:47.643 --> 23:49.166
-MITCH YOU
GOTTA HEAR THIS.

23:49.297 --> 23:50.690
THE GIRL'S BOYFRIEND THINKS
SHE MIGHT BE PREGNANT.

23:51.386 --> 23:52.779
-OH NO.

23:52.909 --> 23:54.345
-AT LEAST THAT'S
WHAT SHE TOLD HIM.

23:54.476 --> 23:56.435
WE COULD BE LOOKING AT
A POSSIBLE SUICIDE HERE.

23:56.565 --> 23:58.611
-ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT.
I'LL GO TALK TO HIM.

24:07.620 --> 24:08.403
-CODY.

24:08.534 --> 24:09.491
WHAT ARE YOU DOIN'?

24:12.799 --> 24:13.800
-GOIN' OUT IN THE WATER.

24:13.930 --> 24:15.105
-WHAT ABOUT MITCH?

24:15.236 --> 24:16.237
-I DON'T GIVE A
DAMN ABOUT MITCH.

24:21.242 --> 24:22.461
-THOUGHT I TOLD
YOU TO GO HOME.

24:23.244 --> 24:24.114
-I CAN'T.

24:25.768 --> 24:26.987
NOT UNTIL WE FIND HER.

24:27.553 --> 24:28.989
LOOK, I KNOW YOU THINK THIS
WHOLE THING'S MY FAULT--

24:29.119 --> 24:30.077
-NO, I DIDN'T SAY THAT.

24:30.207 --> 24:31.644
-NOT IN SO MANY WORDS.

24:31.774 --> 24:33.167
THAT'S THE GENERAL
PERCEPTION AROUND HERE.

24:33.297 --> 24:34.821
-THE GENERAL PERCEPTION
AROUND HERE IS THAT

24:34.951 --> 24:36.518
YOU'RE OUTTA CONTROL.

24:36.649 --> 24:37.345
-FOR CRYIN' OUT LOUD
MITCH, ALL I'M ASKIN' TO DO

24:37.476 --> 24:38.564
IS TO LET ME HELP.

24:39.347 --> 24:42.393
LOOK, I KNOW I FLEW OFF THE
HANDLE BEFORE AND I'M SORRY.

24:42.524 --> 24:45.179
AND I HAVE TO ACCEPT
RESPONSIBILITY FOR MY ACTIONS

24:45.309 --> 24:47.573
BUT I ALSO THINK I DESERVE
TO BE PART OF THE RESCUE.

24:48.661 --> 24:49.488
-ALL RIGHT.

24:49.618 --> 24:50.837
YOU WANNA HELP?

24:50.967 --> 24:52.229
GET EVERYBODY
OUT OF THE WATER.

24:53.143 --> 24:54.275
-OUT OF THE WATER?

24:54.405 --> 24:55.842
-GET EVERYBODY
OUT OF THE WATER.

24:57.408 --> 24:59.193
NO LONGER A
RESCUE OPERATION.

25:00.281 --> 25:01.891
IT'S A RECOVERY OPERATION.

25:03.066 --> 25:04.241
I WANT EVERYBODY ASSEMBLED.

25:05.329 --> 25:06.243
AND A HUMAN CHAIN.

25:09.420 --> 25:10.944
-MANNY: SEÑORA ALVAREZ.

25:13.729 --> 25:15.122
[SPEAKING IN SPANISH]

25:15.862 --> 25:16.863
-LIFEGUARD: COME
ON SWEETIE.

25:19.605 --> 25:21.868
-[MANNY SPEAKING SPANISH]

25:24.044 --> 25:27.830
-TELL HER THAT BECAUSE
SO MUCH TIME HAS PASSED...

25:29.832 --> 25:32.095
I DON'T THINK THERE'S
MUCH CHANCE IN FINDING

25:32.226 --> 25:34.315
HER DAUGHTER ALIVE.

25:38.972 --> 25:43.716
-[MANNY SPEAKING SPANISH]

25:56.511 --> 25:57.904
-TELL HER WE'LL
CONTINUE TO LOOK

25:58.687 --> 26:00.384
FOR THE LITTLE GIRL
UNTIL IT GETS DARK.

26:01.037 --> 26:02.343
AND THAT WE'RE
REALLY SORRY.

26:03.692 --> 26:08.828
-[MANNY SPEAKING SPANISH]

26:25.714 --> 26:26.759
-MITCH: IT'S OKAY.

26:27.324 --> 26:28.325
IT'S OKAY.

26:34.201 --> 26:39.336
-[WOMAN SPEAKING SPANISH]

26:42.992 --> 26:47.431
-[MANNY SPEAKING SPANISH]

26:51.784 --> 26:53.089
WHAT'D SHE SAY?

26:53.220 --> 26:54.308
-SHE SAID THAT SHE
WOULD LIKE TO STAY

26:56.049 --> 26:57.441
AND PRAY FOR A MIRACLE.

26:58.094 --> 26:59.313
-TELL HER IT'S
OKAY, HUH?

27:01.054 --> 27:03.360
YOU STAY WITH HER, I'M GONNA
GO CHECK ON THE LITTLE GIRL.

27:30.431 --> 27:31.650
-WHY ARE WE STARTIN' HERE?

27:32.389 --> 27:33.695
-THIS IS WHERE THE
CURRENT WAS PULLING FROM.

27:33.826 --> 27:34.957
IT'S A GOOD ANCHOR POINT.

27:35.566 --> 27:37.177
WE'LL WORK OUR WAY
DOWN FROM HERE.

27:37.307 --> 27:39.222
-AND WITH ALL THESE LIFEGUARDS
AND ALL THIS EQUIPMENT

27:39.353 --> 27:40.833
YOU'D THINK SHE'D
OF TURNED UP BY NOW.

27:41.747 --> 27:43.183
-ALL RIGHT, EVERYONE.

27:43.313 --> 27:45.402
WE'RE GOING TO BE DOING
A BOX PATTERN SEARCH.

27:46.055 --> 27:49.929
2WE'RE GONNA TAKE TEN STEPS TO
THE WEST, THEN TO THE NORTH,

27:50.625 --> 27:52.714
AND THEN BACK IN EAST
TO THE BEACH AGAIN.

27:52.845 --> 27:54.890
WE'LL REGROUP, AND
START OVER AGAIN.

27:55.543 --> 27:57.023
ALL RIGHT, JOIN HANDS.

27:58.154 --> 27:58.981
LET'S GO.

27:59.112 --> 28:03.986
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

28:44.592 --> 28:46.637
-I DON'T KNOW ABOUT YOU
GUYS, BUT I CAN'T SEE A THING.

28:57.605 --> 28:59.955
-OH, UH, YOU GUYS.

29:00.086 --> 29:01.261
I THINK I FOUND HER.

29:03.785 --> 29:05.047
-NEWMAN: HEY, EASY!

29:20.759 --> 29:22.761
ALRIGHT GUYS LET'S
FORM UP THE LINE AGAIN.

29:24.545 --> 29:28.114
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

29:32.466 --> 29:36.122
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

30:13.942 --> 30:15.204
-AND SO, AS
SUNDOWN APPROACHES,

30:15.335 --> 30:17.728
STILL NO SIGN OF
THE MISSING GIRL.

30:17.859 --> 30:20.253
WE'LL BE HERE AS LONG AS
THIS SEARCH CONTINUES.

30:20.383 --> 30:22.211
BUT OBVIOUSLY, WE HAVE
A GROUP OF VERY TIRED

30:22.342 --> 30:25.388
AND FRUSTRATED LIFEGUARDS
HERE, WHO ARE SIMPLY

30:25.519 --> 30:26.955
RUNNING OUT OF TIME.

30:27.086 --> 30:28.652
THIS IS HARVEY NORRIS,
REPORTING LIVE FROM

30:28.783 --> 30:31.177
SUNSET BEACH. BACK
TO YOU IN THE STUDIO.

30:32.221 --> 30:33.744
.-CAMERAMAN: AND
WE'RE CLEAR.

30:33.875 --> 30:35.224
-ALRIGHT LISTEN,
COME HERE.

30:35.355 --> 30:36.225
WE GOTTA GET ONE
MORE THING OVER HERE.

30:39.925 --> 30:44.494
-[MAN YELLING
ON MEGAPHONE]

31:01.468 --> 31:03.383
-TEN MORE FEET
AND WE TURN, OKAY?

31:03.513 --> 31:04.297
-CODY: YEAH.

31:04.427 --> 31:05.385
-[APRIL SCREAMS]

31:05.515 --> 31:06.560
-WHAT'S WRONG?

31:06.690 --> 31:07.866
-SOMETHING JUST BIT ME!

31:08.867 --> 31:09.737
-CHRIS, HELP ME.

31:12.000 --> 31:12.871
-I GOT HER.

31:16.222 --> 31:17.571
-NEWMAN: OKAY LET'S
GET HER TO THE BEACH.

31:18.311 --> 31:19.138
YOU GUYS KEEP LOOKING.

31:19.268 --> 31:20.139
-ALL RIGHT, LET'S GO.

31:24.317 --> 31:27.450
-[PEOPLE TALKING]

31:52.606 --> 31:53.694
-THAT'S IT.

31:56.262 --> 31:57.567
WE'RE THROUGH FOR TODAY.

32:04.618 --> 32:05.706
-THEY'LL BE
BACK TOMORROW.

32:11.320 --> 32:12.539
-MAÑANA.

32:14.410 --> 32:19.415
-[SAD MUSIC]

32:47.313 --> 32:48.227
GO ON, GO HOME.

32:48.357 --> 32:49.228
I MEAN IT.

32:49.358 --> 32:50.707
YOU'LL GET HYPOTHERMIA.

32:51.273 --> 32:52.231
-I'LL BE OKAY.

32:53.188 --> 32:54.973
JUST FIVE MORE MINUTES.

33:18.126 --> 33:19.867
-[PHONE RINGING]

33:19.998 --> 33:20.999
-BUCHANNON'S OFFICE.

33:22.348 --> 33:23.436
YEAH HOLD ON HE'S
JUST COMIN' IN.

33:23.566 --> 33:25.568
-WHOEVER IT IS,
NO COMMENT.

33:26.569 --> 33:27.875
-IT'S THE CHIEF.

33:28.484 --> 33:30.356
-[GROANS]

33:31.748 --> 33:33.185
-PUT HER ON THE SPEAKER.

33:33.707 --> 33:34.925
-HERE HE IS.

33:36.144 --> 33:37.624
-CHIEF: WHAT'S
YOUR STATUS?

33:38.146 --> 33:39.452
-SHUTDOWN TIL MORNING.

33:40.235 --> 33:41.280
-MITCH YOU LEFT
THESE ON THE BEACH.

33:41.410 --> 33:42.759
-CHIEF: WHO'S THAT?

33:42.890 --> 33:43.934
AND WHY DO YOU HAVE
ME ON THE SPEAKER?

33:44.065 --> 33:45.719
-BECAUSE I'M TOO
TIRED TO MOVE.

33:45.849 --> 33:47.895
-I'M SORRY, DO YOU NEED
ME FOR ANYTHING ELSE?

33:48.026 --> 33:49.505
-NO, NO, NO, THANKS.

33:49.636 --> 33:50.463
NOW GO ON GET
OUT OF HERE.

33:50.593 --> 33:51.812
WE'LL SEE YA TOMORROW.

33:51.942 --> 33:52.769
-WELL I'M NOT ON
SCHEDULE BUT I'LL BE IN.

33:53.988 --> 33:56.208
-CHIEF: DO YOU HAVE
CODY'S RESIGNATION YET?

33:57.339 --> 33:59.037
-NO.

33:59.167 --> 34:00.473
-CHIEF: I WANT IT ON MY DESK
FIRST THING IN THE MORNING

34:00.603 --> 34:01.213
OR I'LL COME DOWN
THERE AND PERSONALLY

34:01.343 --> 34:02.823
FIRE HIM MYSELF!

34:02.953 --> 34:04.259
-YOU WANNA FIRE SOMEBODY,
JUST FIRE ME, HUH?

34:04.955 --> 34:06.914
+BECAUSE I'M THE IDIOT
WHO WAS WASTING HIS TIME

34:07.045 --> 34:08.524
TO SOME MINDLESS
BUDGET MEETING,

34:08.655 --> 34:09.525
WHEN I SHOULDA BEEN ON
THE BEACH WHERE I BELONG!

34:09.656 --> 34:10.960
4AND YOU KNOW WHY?

34:11.092 --> 34:12.876
BECAUSE FOR SOME
INEXPLICABLE REASON

34:13.007 --> 34:15.053
I LET YOU TALK ME
INTO BECOMING CAPTAIN!

34:15.183 --> 34:16.141
WELL I HATE IT!

34:16.271 --> 34:17.751
I'M SICK OF IT!

34:17.880 --> 34:19.708
I HATE THIS OFFICE, I
HATE THESE DAMN PANTS,

34:19.840 --> 34:24.366
I HATE THIS SHIRT, AND MOST OF
ALL I HATE THESE DAMN SHOES!

34:25.237 --> 34:26.194
-CHIEF: MITCH!

34:26.760 --> 34:29.893
MITCH, WHAT IN GOD'S
NAME IS GOING ON THERE?

34:30.545 --> 34:32.070
SOUNDS LIKE YOU
NEED A NEW WINDOW.

34:32.809 --> 34:33.679
-NO.

34:34.376 --> 34:35.464
YOU NEED A NEW CAPTAIN.

34:35.594 --> 34:38.076
-[PHONE SLAMS ON FLOOR]

34:41.208 --> 34:42.297
-[SIGHS]

34:42.428 --> 34:43.646
WHAT!?

34:48.650 --> 34:53.091
[SLOW RELAXING MUSIC]

37:31.161 --> 37:32.554
-MITCH.

37:32.685 --> 37:33.729
YOU'VE GOTTA GO HOME
AND GET SOME SLEEP.

37:34.252 --> 37:35.601
YOU'VE GOT THIS TO DO
ALL OVER AGAIN TOMORROW.

37:37.777 --> 37:38.734
-YOU'RE RIGHT.

37:41.650 --> 37:42.738
-[PHONE RINGING]

37:42.869 --> 37:43.913
-I'LL GET IT.

37:46.089 --> 37:47.177
BAYWATCH HEADQUARTERS.

37:48.353 --> 37:49.310
WHAT?

37:49.832 --> 37:50.703
UH-HUH.

37:55.316 --> 37:59.973
-[TRIUMPHANT MUSIC]

38:16.685 --> 38:17.599
-HEY.

38:22.256 --> 38:23.257
THEY FOUND HER.

38:25.085 --> 38:28.001
WHEN THEY WENT
HOME, SHE WAS THERE.

38:29.002 --> 38:30.003
-YOU'RE KIDDING ME.

38:31.178 --> 38:32.005
-NO I'M NOT.

38:32.135 --> 38:33.485
WE JUST GOT THE CALL.

38:34.486 --> 38:35.661
-THANK GOD.

38:35.791 --> 38:36.749
-HOW DID SHE--

38:36.879 --> 38:38.707
-I DON'T KNOW, I DON'T KNOW.

38:38.838 --> 38:42.058
APPARENTLY SHE SWAM OUT,
WENT AROUND THE ROCKS,

38:42.189 --> 38:46.193
SNUCK OUT OF THE OCEAN
AND CAUGHT A BUS HOME.

38:50.589 --> 38:51.677
-I DON'T KNOW
WHAT TO SAY.

38:52.330 --> 38:53.287
-HEY MAN.

38:56.029 --> 38:57.552
YOU DON'T HAVE
TO SAY ANYTHING.

38:59.249 --> 39:04.385
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

39:14.917 --> 39:19.357
-[UPBEAT MUSIC]

39:27.234 --> 39:28.801
-[GRUNTS]

39:35.329 --> 39:37.331
THIS IS LIEUTENANT
BUCHANNON, I AM HERE AT

39:37.462 --> 39:39.594
TOWER 15, IF ANYONE
WANTS TO GET AHOLD OF ME

39:39.725 --> 39:41.379
I'LL BE HERE ALL DAY.

39:42.118 --> 39:42.902
THANKS.

39:43.032 --> 39:43.946
YOU TOO.

39:47.210 --> 39:48.951
[SIGHS]

39:51.693 --> 39:52.738
HEY CODY!

39:52.868 --> 39:53.695
-HEY MAN.

39:54.217 --> 39:55.088
WHAT'S GOIN' ON?

39:57.046 --> 39:57.917
-MITCH: YOU SEE
THE LETTER?

39:58.483 --> 39:59.484
-NO, WHAT LETTER?

40:00.702 --> 40:04.053
-THE LETTER FROM ROSANNA
ALVAREZ APOLOGIZING FOR

40:04.184 --> 40:06.360
PUTTING ALL THE
LIFEGUARDS THROUGH HELL.

40:07.405 --> 40:09.494
ANYWAY, IF YOU WANNA SEE IT,
IT'S ON THE BULLETIN BOARD.

40:10.016 --> 40:10.973
-I'LL CHECK IT OUT.

40:11.974 --> 40:13.019
SO WHAT'S GONNA HAPPEN?

40:13.976 --> 40:15.238
I DON'T KNOW WHICH
RUMOR TO BELIEVE.

40:15.369 --> 40:17.153
I'M EITHER BEING
FIRED, SUSPENDED, OR

40:17.284 --> 40:18.285
BEING MADE
THE NEW CAPTAIN.

40:19.068 --> 40:21.375
-WELL I DID TALK
TO THE CHIEF. UM,

40:21.897 --> 40:24.117
SHE IS NOT A REAL
BIG FAN OF YOURS.

40:25.335 --> 40:28.904
NEVERTHELESS, I DID CONVINCE
HER THAT A LETTER OF REPRIMAND

40:29.035 --> 40:30.384
WAS THE MOST FITTING
FORM OF PUNISHMENT.

40:30.515 --> 40:31.646
-REALLY?

40:31.777 --> 40:32.560
1THAT'S IT?

40:32.691 --> 40:33.866
-NO.

40:33.996 --> 40:35.389
SHE WANTS YOU SUSPENDED
FOR TWO WEEKS.

40:35.520 --> 40:36.390
-TWO WEEKS?

40:36.521 --> 40:37.565
-YEAH.

40:39.175 --> 40:40.307
-YOU THINK THAT'S FAIR?

40:40.960 --> 40:44.006
-BASICALLY, YEAH, BUT THAT'S
NOT REALLY THE ISSUE HERE.

40:44.790 --> 40:47.357
WHAT THE ISSUE HERE IS,
IS THAT YOUR SUSPENSION

40:48.054 --> 40:50.448
CREATES AN OPENING
IN THE SCHEDULE.

40:50.970 --> 40:53.059
-OH, SO THAT'S WHAT
THIS IS ALL ABOUT.

40:54.016 --> 40:55.801
YOU'D DO ANYTHING TO
GET BACK IN A TOWER.

40:55.931 --> 40:56.802
-YOU GOT IT.

40:59.544 --> 41:01.241
-SO HOW'S IT
FEEL, LIEUTENANT?

41:01.371 --> 41:04.026
-FEELS ABSOLUTELY GREAT.

41:04.679 --> 41:05.854
-RIGHT ON.

41:05.985 --> 41:07.508
WELL, SEE YA
IN A COUPLE WEEKS.

41:07.639 --> 41:08.509
-OKAY.

41:09.510 --> 41:11.469
-HEY AND UH, DON'T
GET TOO COMFORTABLE.

41:11.599 --> 41:12.992
I WANT MY SCHEDULE BACK.

41:13.122 --> 41:14.210
-ALL RIGHT.

41:14.341 --> 41:18.911
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

41:44.806 --> 41:48.593
--[END THEME PLAYS]
